  ##If you're coming to work in an eligible skilled job

  The visa you need usually depends on whether you're coming to work:

  + for the National Health Service (NHS), an NHS supplier or in adult social care - you may be eligible for the [Health and Care Worker visa](https://www.gov.uk/health-care-worker-visa)
  + for any other organisation or type of healthcare - you may be eligible for the [Skilled Worker visa](https://www.gov.uk/skilled-worker-visa)

  ###Eligibility

  The eligibility criteria for both visas includes:

  - working in an eligible job, for example a doctor or a nurse
  - having a job offer
  - being paid a minimum salary - how much depends on the type of work you do
  - usually proving that you can read, write, speak and understand English

  ###How long you can stay

  Both visas can last for up to 5 years. You can extend your visa as long as you're still eligible.

  After 5 years, you may be able to apply to settle permanently in the UK.

